The paper discusses the challenges of handling geospatial big data and the use of high performance computing (HPC) to address these challenges. The topic of big data is often associated with database systems (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC), which are both relevant to this paper. The use of HPC also suggests a focus on computational engineering (cs.CE) and scientific computing (cs.SE). Additionally, the processing and analysis of large datasets is a common theme in data science (cs.DS).
